-CREATE A VPC PEERING CONNECTION
-ADD ROUTE IN THE ROUTE TABLES
-VPC PEERING CAN BE DONE TO PARTICULAR SUBNETS USING THOSE SUBNET IPS ONLY
-TO IMPORT SAME KEY PAIR FROM ONE REGION TO ANOTHER:
  -OPEN SERVER AND COMMAND:ec2-met(press tab)
  -COPY THE PASSWORD AND IMPORT TO OTHER REGION
-USE ONLY THESE IPS FOR VPC(CIDR/16)
  -10.0.0.0 TO 10.255.255.255
  -172.16.0.0 TO 172.31.255.255
  -192.168.0.0 TO 192.168.255.255
  -10.0.0.0/8 - 16MILLION IPS
  -10.0.0.0/16 - 65000 IPS
  -10.0.0.0./24 - 255 IPS
-IN ANY SUBNETTING FOR EG-10.0.1.0/24, YOU DONT HAVE TOTAL 255IPS, AS 0 AND 255 ARE NETWORK AND BRODCASTING ID, 1,2,3 IPS IS USED BY AMAZON FOR INTERNAL PURPOSE.




#CANNOT SUPPORT IN TRANSIT
#CANNOT ACCEPT SAME IPS OF TWO VPCS
#TOTAL VPCS PER REGION - 5
#SUBENTS PER VPC - 200
#IPV4 CIDR BLOCKS PER VPC - 4
#IPV6 CIDR BLOCKS PER VPC -1
#INTERNET GATEWAYS PER REGION - 5
#NAT GATEWAYS PER AVAILABILITY ZONE - 5
#NACLS PER VPC - 200
#NACLS RULES PER NETWORK - 20
#NETWORK INTERFACES PER REGION - 5000
#SECURITY GRPS PER REGION - 2500
#INBOUND/OUTBOUND RULES PER SG - 60
#GATEWAY ENDPOINTS PER REGION - 20
#INTERFAE ENDPOINTS PER VPC -50
#ACTIVE VPC PEERING CONNECTIONS -50
#EXPIRY TIME FOR A VPC PEERING - 1WEEK(168HRS)
#VPC ENDPOINT POLICY SIZE - 20,480CHARACTERS
